uk.ac.ebi.mdk.io.text.biocyc
Class AttributedEntry<K,V>

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ebi.mdk.io.text.biocyc.AttributedEntry<K,V>

public class AttributedEntry<K,V>
extends Object

Simple class that provides the functionality of Mulitmap (see. Guava util library). The primary use for the class is in parsing text attributed files (e.g. KEGG/BioCyc). In addition to providing multi-map functionality it also has some convenience methods such as isFilled() and renew(). The later (renew()) is convenient for parsing files.

Author:
John May

renew

public AttributedEntry<K,V> renew()
Create a shallow copy of this entry and clear the current entry. This functionality is useful when you need to pre-load and entry when parsing. Using this method it is possible to keep pre-loading into the same entry and then when an actual entry is required the renew method will renew a mutable entry.

Returns:
shallow copy
